text: Windsor County is a county in Vermont in the United States. At the 2020 census, 57,753 people lived there. Its shire town (county seat) is the town of Woodstock, and largest municipality is the town of Hartford. == References == Category:Vermont counties Category:1781 establishments in North America Category:1780s establishments in the United States Category:18th-century establishments in Vermont
